# No Internal Details in UI

Never show infrastructure, credentials, env vars, ports, or setup instructions in user-facing UI (footers, banners, tooltips, etc.). This is a production product.

## Forbidden in rendered JSX

- API keys, env var names (`BEDROCK_REGION`, `VALSEA_API_KEY`, etc.)
- Server ports or hostnames (`port 8001`, `127.0.0.1`)
- Setup instructions (`.env`, `uvicorn`, `pip install`)
- Internal service names (`FastAPI`, `Bedrock`, `Valsea`)
- File paths or config references

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
<footer>Set AWS credentials in .env · FastAPI on port 8001</footer>
<p>Powered by Valsea + AWS Bedrock</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<footer>Lecture2Quiz SEA</footer>
<footer>© 2026 Lecture2Quiz SEA</footer>
```

Keep all infra/setup details in README.md and `.env.example` only.
